{"id":6388,"title":"Site directed mutagenesis by PCR","title_html":"Site directed mutagenesis by PCR","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/default_protocol.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/default_protocol.png"},"doi":"dx.doi.org\/10.17504\/protocols.io.igucbww","doi_status":2,"uri":"site-directed-mutagenesis-by-pcr-igucbww","type_id":1,"published_on":1567603914,"parent_protocols":[],"parent_collections":[],"version_id":0,"created_on":1497520796,"categories":null,"creator":{"name":"Tobias von der Haar","affiliation":"","affiliations":[{"affiliation":"","url":"","is_default":1}],"username":"tobias-von-der-haar","link":null,"image":{"source":"\/img\/avatars\/005.png","placeholder":"\/img\/avatars\/005.png"},"badges":[{"id":3,"image":{"source":"\/img\/badges\/silver.svg","placeholder":"\/img\/badges\/silver.svg"},"name":"Power author!"},{"id":5,"image":{"source":"\/img\/badges\/earlyadopter.svg","placeholder":"\/img\/badges\/earlyadopter.svg"},"name":"Early adopter"}],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false},"journal":null,"journal_name":null,"journal_link":null,"article_citation":null,"public":1,"has_versions":0,"link":"","total_collections":0,"number_of_steps":4,"authors":[{"name":"Tobias von der Haar","affiliation":"University of Kent at Canterbury","affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":null,"placeholder":null},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false}],"versions":[],"groups":[],"has_subprotocols":0,"is_subprotocol":0,"is_bookmarked":0,"can_be_copied":1,"can_remove_fork":1,"forks_count":{"private":0,"public":0},"access":{"can_view":1,"can_remove":0,"can_add":0,"can_edit":0,"can_publish":0,"can_get_doi":0,"can_share":1,"can_move":1,"can_move_outside":1,"can_transfer":1,"can_download":1,"is_locked":0},"steps":[{"id":574579,"guid":"F56BF5BA7B844846BD1E618F7D64F3DC","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"5FD2ACD247A44E5281D19CAA51EA076A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"7F8E6D3B946D4A68BCE9DBB6AB836107","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Design four primers in the following way:\u00a0<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/kh5fnq6.png\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Primer 1 anneals upstream of the region to be mutated<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Primer 2 anneals downstream of the region to be mutated, in reverse direction, and has a 6 nt mismatch to the target at its\u00a03'-end.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Primer 3 anneals downstream of primer 2 (not overlapping with the primer 2 site).<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Primer M anneals of the site to be mutated, containing the mutation itself and\u00a015 nt on either side of the mutation.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">If Primers 1, 2 and 3 are designed to anneal to vector sequences 5\u2019 and 3\u2019 of a multiple cloning site, they can be reused for any mutagenesis performed in this vector.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":574582,"guid":"7F23BC6A0F4B4C18B77A293D475C973E","previous_id":574579,"previous_guid":"F56BF5BA7B844846BD1E618F7D64F3DC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"150C656FF1FD416BBADB7D69896F2786","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"65B91F5BD05C403E95CB4B87F4BE8C50","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Perform two PCR reactions with your template DNA: the first with primers 1 and 2, the second with primers M and 3.\u00a0You should use a proof-reading polymerase that does not append 'A' overhangs to the pCR product - if you use Taq polymerase, the nucleotide before the primer annealing site for primer M must be a T (this will allow base-peiring with the A residues appended to PCR products by Taq).<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Clean up the PCR products by resolbing them on an agarose gel, excising the bands, and using a gel extraction kit to retrieve the DNA.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":574584,"guid":"0E2186A80BC947ED920C16D1B7655455","previous_id":574582,"previous_guid":"7F23BC6A0F4B4C18B77A293D475C973E","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B139568A679649068BFE46845498862F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"BE18BA813DD04324BDD179EC48513A19","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Perform the second round PCR,\u00a0using primers 1 and 3, and ~1\u00a0\u03bcl each of the two PCR producst from round 1 as template.<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/kh4fnq6.png\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">In the initial rounds of the PCR, the\u00a0two product will anneal and the\u00a0product incorporating the mutation can be extended to full length - this\u00a0contains annealing sites for both primers 1 and 3, and will be amplified in subsequent rounds. The other strand cannot be extended to full length due to the 3'-end mismatch.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":574587,"guid":"0B0CC66E46BB49509AD26AE2B47B76A2","previous_id":574584,"previous_guid":"0E2186A80BC947ED920C16D1B7655455","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"5151F773B57F4652B2439315E30AAD54","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"D1BE591CF4C94EDCABA7B0ABBD7B84A4","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Use the final PCR product for cloning \u00a0as for any other PCR product.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><\/div>","changed_on":1567603914}